10/07/2006
TIRANA, Albania -- Eight suspected drug traffickers have been arrested in Albania following a joint operation conducted with Italy and Turkey, officials in Tirana announced on Friday (7 July). 
The eight allegedly ran a channel trafficking heroin from Turkey to Italy via Albania. 
An agent with the anti-drug police department in Tirana allegedly also was involved and faces charges of revealing state secrets.
In other news, Macedonian authorities extradited Lulzim Berisha to Albania on Sunday on the basis of an international arrest warrant. 
In April, he was arrested in Tetovo with a forged passport. 
Berisha is wanted for the murders of six people and other crimes in Albania. 
(Albanian News - 10/07/06; Gazeta sot - 08/07/06)
